{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a90a989d-408b-41f9-8ae7-007e252121eb","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle event mappings** on `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in your `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* runs on Android OnPause */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* runs on Android OnStop */ }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* runs on iOS DidEnterBackground */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Platform directives (`#if ANDROID`, `#if IOS`) keep the code compiling on all targets.\n- Other mappings are available too — e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, etc.\n- These handlers receive the native platform object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS), so you can call native APIs directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27cef74b-c156-4e6a-b415-7a39c8743a14","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":353,"requestId":"3C25:A0D2E:D2B8D9:106FEF7:6A0129B7"},"id":"9fb96916-b653-43d3-b27f-56f1f01a0137","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:40.130Z","parentId":"7f8c111c-bea6-4f5c-944d-237143f603ee"}
